{"parse":{"title":"Bellwether trial","pageid":37285625,"revid":823329027,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In the law of <a href=\"/wiki/Tort\" title=\"Tort\">torts</a>, <b>bellwether trial</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Test_case_(law)\" title=\"Test case (law)\">test case</a> intended to try a widely contested issue.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Bellwether <a href=\"/wiki/Trial\" title=\"Trial\">trials</a> are an increasingly common phenomenon in <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">U.S.</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Practice_of_law\" title=\"Practice of law\">legal practice</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Bellwether trials are especially common in <a href=\"/wiki/Multidistrict_Litigation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Multidistrict Litigation\">Multidistrict Litigation</a> (MDL) practice, where many cases have been consolidated for purposes of <a href=\"/wiki/Discovery_(law)\" title=\"Discovery (law)\">discovery</a> and pretrial matters. In these MDL cases, it is not practical to prepare every case for trial. Several matters are, therefore, selected as bellwether cases and prepared for trial. They are then settled or tried and the results are used to shape the process for addressing the remaining cases.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>A bellwether trial is designed to achieve value ascertainment function for <a href=\"/wiki/Settlement_(litigation)\" title=\"Settlement (litigation)\">settlement</a> purposes or to answer troubling <a href=\"/wiki/Causation_(law)\" title=\"Causation (law)\">causation</a> or liability issues common to a universe of <a href=\"/wiki/Plaintiff\" title=\"Plaintiff\">claimants</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> For the tried cases to achieve these purposes, it must be representative of all cases.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bellwether_trial&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Alexandra D. Lahav. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://works.bepress.com/alexandra_lahav/3/\">\"Bellwether Trials\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2012-10-10</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Bellwether+Trials&amp;rft.au=Alexandra+D.+Lahav&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fworks.bepress.com%2Falexandra_lahav%2F3%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABellwether+trial\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Jeremy Grabill (May 18, 2011). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://product-liability.weil.com/mass-tort/the-spread-of-bellwether-trials/\">\"The Spread of Bellwether Trials\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2012-10-10</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Spread+of+Bellwether+Trials&amp;rft.date=2011-05-18&amp;rft.au=Jeremy+Grabill&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fproduct-liability.weil.com%2Fmass-tor